an class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uvlieke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vlieke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer of Victus Fortis</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#8B4513>(10/8/01 7:21:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Monk purple headband / Permafrost</span><hr size=1> One item left in monk headband/sash series.  The coronet of buried blood carried by High Priest Zaharn in Permafrost.<br>
<br>
I did some covert ops there the other day, but was unable to obtain the item.  I did however sneak into the King's Room where he spawns and check things out.  Had to evac when a train came through though.<br>
<br>
So I'd appreciate any support you can lend to the cause.  I plan on heading in there this coming Saturday at 8 AM U.S. CST = 2 PM GMT = 11 PM AUS STANDARD TIME.  With the time zone spread, this should allow players everywhere to come along if they want to.  Also, it will be early U.S. time and should be fairly free of farmers.  (&lt;---- wow, alliteration)<br>
<br>
The King room has a half dozen or so low 30's mobs.  They are primarily casters so MR gear is good to bring along.  Crowd control would be useful here, too, in the tight quarters.<br>
<br>
I don't want to call this a raid.  But, the more people that show up, the greater our ability to explore this intriquing zone.  For Zaharn, all that's needed is one well-balanced group of 28-35.<br>
<br>
One great thing about Permafrost, though, is that there is adventure here for players levels 15-60.  So no matter what level you are, there will be something to do.<br>
<br>
Please post here if you are interested.  If 2 or or 3 groups of people want to come, then we can discuss what areas of the dungeon we'd like to explore and develop a plan with a little more detail.<br>
<br>
BTW, 13% xp bonus here.  Thanks all,<br>
<br>
S.F.J.<br>
<br>
P.S.  If you can't make it at the time indicated but are interested, give a rough idea here of your schedule for that day.  Thanks!<br>
<br>
